subSubSection.paragraph:
The new species is similar to 
P. bailongensis
, and can be distinguished by the strongly reduced eyes and pale yellow abdomen (Figs 3A, 4A) (eyes well-developed and abdomen greenish in 
P. bailongensis
); shorter embolus, about 0.38 of the bulb length (0.59 of the bulb length in 
P. bailongensis
) (Figs 3
C-D
, 7C, 8C, 9C, 10C); receptacle coiled approximately 270° (Fig. 4C) (approximately 450° in 
P. bailongensis
); the 1st and 2nd setae on cymbial apophysis located at the same height (Fig. 12C) (setae at different heights in 
P. bailongensis
).
